Popular disc jockey Cuppy has pledged to sponsor the university education of an 18-year-old girl. In a video shared on her Instagram page, the billionaire heiress was seen backstage with a girl who held unto her while they spoke after sharing a hug at a video shoot in Lagos. The girl, who identified as Oluwatobiloba told Cuppy she wasn’t in school because she lost her dad and was trying to work in order to make ends meet.   I Go Dye unveils artists for Benin Easter Sunday show     Mr Eazi receives £1,000 as engagement gift     Osinachi’s death: Marriage good but not by force…   Tobi in the course of her discussion with DJ Cuppy revealed she would love to study hospitality in the university after the latter stressed on being a lover of education. Captioning her post, the “Gelato” singer noted God orchestrated her meeting with Tobi so her life could be transformed while she pledged to sponsor her university education through her foundation. “I feel like God wanted me to meet Tobi so I could change her life…. She was behind the scenes catering during my Pepsi photo shoot. At 18 years old, her resilience after such a life tragedy inspired me! Best believe Tobi IS going to school and the @CuppyFoundation will provide EVERY resource she needs until she graduates!” Cuppy wrote.